SIMPLE: redub
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redub
<hw>Re*dub"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*d⟦ucr⟧b")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>radouber</ets> to refit or repair.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
refit; to repair, or make reparation for; hence, to repay or
requite.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It shall be good that you <qex>redub</qex> that negligence.</q>
<rj><qau>Wyatt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God shall give power to <qex>redub</qex> it with some like
requital to the French.</q> <rj><qau>Grafton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dub again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reduce</ent>⟦br⟧
